# This directory is the Traefik "file" provider's mount point. It is read by
# the proxy container at /etc/traefik/dynamic and watched for changes at
# runtime (no restart needed when files are added or modified).
#
# Add .yml or .toml files here for routing rules that aren't container-scoped
# — for example: routing to an external upstream, global middlewares, or
# TLS certificate definitions before Let's Encrypt is wired in.
#
# Empty at M1. Populated at M4 if needed for the integrated data services.
